{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17657671","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17657671"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:32:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:32:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20594"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"20594","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/20594"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.6,0.05,0.05,0.2,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13471"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"93792"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"13471","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13471"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20594"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"77002"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"4914"},{"type":"tags","id":"12505"},{"type":"tags","id":"12795"},{"type":"tags","id":"12797"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"32171"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32176"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"93792","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/93792"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old man with advanced HIV infection presents with multiple red-purple patches, plaques and nodules on his skin that have developed over the past month. Biopsy of one lesion shows proliferation of spindle cells forming slit-like vascular spaces with extravasated red blood cells and haemosiderin deposition.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most likely to be the causative agent of this condition?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Human herpesvirus 8","Human papillomavirus","Mycobacterium avium complex","Epstein-Barr virus","Cytomegalovirus"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHuman herpesvirus 8\u003C/strong\u003E (HHV-8), also known as Kaposi sarcoma-associated herpesvirus (KSHV), is the causative agent of Kaposi sarcoma. This virus infects endothelial cells and induces their proliferation, resulting in the characteristic vascular lesions. Kaposi sarcoma is an AIDS-defining illness and is one of the most common malignancies in patients with advanced HIV infection. Histologically, Kaposi sarcoma is characterised by proliferation of spindle cells, slit-like vascular spaces, extravasated red blood cells, and haemosiderin deposition.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are less likely causes:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHuman papillomavirus\u003C/strong\u003E is associated with cervical, anal, and oropharyngeal cancers in HIV-infected patients, but not with Kaposi sarcoma. It causes epithelial proliferation rather than vascular lesions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMycobacterium avium complex\u003C/strong\u003E is an opportunistic infection in HIV patients but typically causes disseminated disease with fever, weight loss, lymphadenopathy, and hepatosplenomegaly rather than vascular proliferative skin lesions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEpstein-Barr virus\u003C/strong\u003E is associated with several lymphoproliferative disorders in HIV-infected patients, including non-Hodgkin lymphoma and primary central nervous system lymphoma, but not Kaposi sarcoma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECytomegalovirus\u003C/strong\u003E can cause retinitis, colitis, pneumonitis, and encephalitis in HIV-infected patients but is not associated with Kaposi sarcoma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EKaposi sarcoma has four clinical variants: classic (elderly men of Mediterranean or Eastern European descent), endemic (African), transplant-associated, and AIDS-associated. The AIDS-associated variant is typically more aggressive and widespread than the other forms.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Kaposi sarcoma is caused by human herpesvirus 8 (HHV-8) infection.","Kaposi sarcoma presents as red-purple patches, plaques or nodules with characteristic histological findings of spindle cell proliferation and slit-like vascular spaces.","Kaposi sarcoma occurs predominantly in immunocompromised individuals, particularly those with HIV infection."],"references":["Mitchell RN, Halushka MK. Blood vessels. In: Kumar V, Abbas AK, Aster JC, editors. Robbins \u0026 Cotran Pathologic Basis of Disease. 10th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2020. p. 485\u2013525."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"77002"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20594"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"77002","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/77002"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-22T14:19:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-22T14:20:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13471"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"93792"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4914","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4914"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Blood vessels","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdA